    <p>Write For Kind­ness 2020</p>
    <p>Se­condary school and ter­tiary stu­dents are in­vited to take part in this com­pe­ti­tion. Form a team of five (sto­ry­writ­ing and il­lus­tra­tion) or two (po­etry writ­ing and il­lus­tra­tion) within your school. All teams must at­tend on­line work­shops to learn fun­da­men­tal skills in writ­ing and il­lus­trat­ing for a younger au­di­ence which are con­ducted by es­tab­lished lo­cal writ­ers and il­lus­tra­tors. Prizes worth up to $250 are up for grabs. The win­ning story will be pub­lished for pre-school cen­tres and the win­ning poem will ap­pear in the Sin­ga­pore Kind­ness Move­ment’s chil­dren’s newslet­ter. The or­gan­i­sa­tion is part­ner­ing the Sin­ga­pore Book Coun­cil for the work­shops, in con­junc­tion with Open: Young Writ­ers Lab.</p>
    <p>On­line Zoom ses­sions Dates for work­shops: Sept 7, 10am - noon (po­etry writ­ing & il­lus­tra­tion); Sept 8 & 9, 2 - 4pm (sto­ry­writ­ing & il­lus­tra­tion) Regis­tra­tion re­quired bit.ly/3g9oZMh</p>
    <p>Net­work­ing Travel Pro­gramme In Ger­many</p>
    <p>The Goethe-In­sti­tut has launched an ini­tia­tive that will al­low both es­tab­lished and emerg­ing founders, lead­ers and man­agers of art spa­ces from South-east Asia, Aus­tralia and New Zealand to net­work with their coun­ter­parts in Ger­many. The pro­gramme fo­cuses on art spa­ces and col­lab­o­ra­tive projects.</p>
    <p>Ap­ply by Aug 31 bit.ly/34juR3k</p>
    <p>HDB Cool Ideas Hack 2020 – De­sign­ing Ideas For The Heartlands Of To­mor­row</p>
    <p>This three-day on­line “hackathon” chal­lenges in­no­va­tors from all walks of life to come to­gether and de­velop tech­nol­ogy-en­abled so­lu­tions that en­cour­age smart and sus­tain­able liv­ing in Hous­ing Board es­tates. Short­listed teams will move on to the four-week Pre-Ac­cel­er­a­tor pro­gramme, de­signed to help them build their busi­ness mod­els and bring their ideas to life with guid­ance and men­tor­ing from global lead­ers and part­ners.</p>
    <p>Sept 18, 5pm - Sept 20, 9pm</p>
    <p>Free thes­tar­tupx.com/ hdb-cool-ideas-hack</p>


